    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Individuals, known in several cultures, who perform the ritual duties of a priest as well as accompanying troops or taking part in war. Examples are in the Aztec culture, where warrior priests carried sacred idols and conducted human sacrifices on the battlefield.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
